---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-22", modifiedDate: "2026-03-24", section: "Compliance & Legal" };
const topics = ["operations"];
export const title = "Cannabis Delivery Rules";
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Delivery Rules" 
  description="Maine cannabis delivery rules for 2026. State regulations, manifest requirements, vehicle security, and compliance for licensed operators."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1586769852836-bc069f19e1b6?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop"
  article={article}
  topics={topics}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Delivery Rules</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Understanding Maine's cannabis delivery regulations</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Cannabis delivery services expand your customer reach beyond the dispensary walls. Maine allows licensed delivery services, giving entrepreneurs an opportunity to serve customers who may not be able to visit a physical <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-locations/">location</a>. Understanding the rules is essential for a successful delivery operation. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">licensing process</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Excellence in Compliance" type="success">
      Mastering this aspect of your business is a badge of professional excellence. It ensures longevity and demonstrates your commitment to the highest standards of the Maine cannabis industry.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>License Requirements</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, delivery requires:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Courier License</strong> - Separate license for delivery operations</li>
        <li><strong>Dispensary License</strong> - If delivering from your own store</li>
        <li><strong>Employee Authorization</strong> - All drivers must be authorized</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Delivery Rules</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Deliver only to verified addresses within Maine</li>
        <li>Age verification required at delivery</li>
        <li>No delivery to public places</li>
        <li>Real-time tracking recommended</li>
        <li>Secure transport required</li>
        <li>Limit on delivery quantities</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Operational Requirements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>GPS tracking on delivery vehicles</li>
        <li>Secure product storage during transport</li>
        <li>Two-person deliveries recommended</li>
        <li>ID verification technology</li>
        <li>Detailed delivery logs</li>
        <li>Cash handling procedures</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compliance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Maintain delivery records</li>
        <li>Follow all transportation regulations</li>
        <li>Ensure product integrity during transport</li>
        <li>Driver background checks</li>
        <li>Vehicle requirements</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Vehicle</td><td>$25,000-50,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Security Equipment</td><td>$5,000-15,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Tracking Systems</td><td>$2,000-5,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Licensing</td><td>$3,000-10,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; color: #1a1a1a; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
